cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses crowd sensing in mobile social networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper proposes incentive mechanisms for maximizing profits of mobile users, which involves game theory concepts. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of mobile devices for sensing services, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of user behavior and preferences on crowd sensing applications, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes mechanisms for aggregating sensing data from multiple mobile devices, which involves distributed computing concepts.
